May I purpose a new kind of helper. We currently have two kinds of helpers: helpers and dynamicHelpers. Given the example:

```
app.helpers({
  obj: {foo: 23, bar: 11}
});
app.render('file.ejs', {locals:{obj:{foo:5}}});
```

obj.bar will no longer be a local within file.ejs. The locals will overwrite the helper obj entirely, rather than just merge it's properties.

However, it would be useful to be able to merge locals with helpers. So with this:

```
app.mergingHelpers({
  obj: {foo: 23, bar:11}
});
app.render('file.ejs', {locals:{obj:{foo:5}}});
```

obj.bar will still equal 11 within file.ejs. This is because mergingHelpers would define helpers that are recursive when locals overwrite them. This means that the locals object will merge with the merginHelpers object recursively.

I think this concept fits nicely with the the current set of two helpers, completing it with helpers, dynamicHelpers and now mergingHelpers! :D

